'''utelnetd''' is [[Article description::a small and efficient stand alone [[Wikipedia:Telnet|Telnet]] server daemon.]] Telnet can be useful for several applications, such as a backup when updating [[SSH]], and configuring industrial grade routers via console cables.

{{Note|Telnet sends data including passwords in plain text.}}

== Installation ==

=== Emerge ===

Install {{Package|net-misc/utelnetd}}:

{{Emerge|utelnetd}}

== Configuration ==

=== Service ===

To automatically start utelnetd at boot:

{{RootCmd|rc-update add utelnetd default}}

To start it immediately:

{{RootCmd|rc-service start}}

== Testing ==

{{Cmd|telnet localhost}}

